  `vehicle_imu` run (~2 Hz), confirming full-rate reconstruction drives the filter.
- `auto` output matches `fifo` output (same row count / values) — FIFO-preferred ladder.
- Cross-validate the reconstruction against the existing sibling tool: rebuild the same
  log's IMU with `ekf_ned_reconstruction.py --imu-source fifo` (or
  `ekf_verification/ekf2/imu_recon.py`) and confirm the FIFO-reconstructed `delta_angle`/
  `delta_velocity` rates match (this is the already-validated reference).
- Regression: a log **without** FIFO (e.g. `/home/choudhury/Downloads/T3D034_torrey_1_lap.ulg`)
  with `--imu-source auto` still works (falls back to `vehicle_imu`); `--imu-source fifo`
  on it raises a clear "FIFO not present" error. Default behavior (no flag) is unchanged
  except `auto` now prefers FIFO when available.
- Sanity-check estimated NED velocity/position in the CSV are finite and physically
  reasonable over the run.
